WEBVTT

00:07.908 --> 00:10.010
* IT'S A RARE CONDITION *

00:10.078 --> 00:11.412
* IN THIS DAY AND AGE *

00:11.479 --> 00:14.815
* TO READ ANY GOOD NEWS
ON THE NEWSPAPER PAGE *

00:14.882 --> 00:18.419
* AND LOVE AND TRADITION
OF THE GRAND DESIGN *

00:18.486 --> 00:22.856
* SOME PEOPLE SAY
IS EVEN HARDER TO FIND *

00:22.923 --> 00:26.127
* WELL, THEN, THERE MUST BE
SOME MAGIC CLUE *

00:26.194 --> 00:30.331
* INSIDE THESE GENTLE WALLS *

00:30.398 --> 00:34.001
* 'CAUSE ALL I SEE
IS A TOWER OF DREAMS *

00:34.068 --> 00:37.738
* REAL LOVE BURSTIN'
OUT OF EVERY SEAM *

00:38.939 --> 00:41.709
* AS DAYS GO BY *

00:41.775 --> 00:45.913
* WE'RE GONNA FILL
OUR HOUSE WITH HAPPINESS *

00:45.979 --> 00:48.649
* THE MOON MAY CRY *

00:48.716 --> 00:52.353
* WE'RE GONNA SMOTHER
THE BLUES WITH TENDERNESS *

00:52.420 --> 00:55.689
* AS DAYS GO BY *

00:55.756 --> 00:59.393
* THERE'S ROOM FOR YOU,
ROOM FOR ME *

00:59.460 --> 01:03.397
* FOR GENTLE HEARTS
AN OPPORTUNITY *

01:03.464 --> 01:06.667
* AS DAYS GO BY *

01:06.734 --> 01:11.372
* IT'S THE BIGGER LOVE
OF THE FAMILY *

01:24.752 --> 01:26.320
LATER, RACHEL.

01:26.387 --> 01:28.222
HITTING THE COURTS
AGAIN?

01:28.289 --> 01:29.857
I'M PLAYING
ALICE GRAYSON.

01:29.923 --> 01:32.760
I WHIP HER BUTT
EVERY TIME.

01:34.762 --> 01:36.397
BUT SHE'S
HALF YOUR AGE.

01:36.464 --> 01:40.000
POOR THING CAN'T
GO TO THE NET.

01:40.067 --> 01:41.101
LATER, HONEY.

01:41.169 --> 01:42.470
HAVE FUN.

01:47.508 --> 01:49.710
GIVE ME
ONE OF THOSE.

01:50.444 --> 01:51.645
ONE?

02:07.628 --> 02:08.529
WHEW!

02:08.596 --> 02:12.099
THESE GROCERY BAGS...
ARE HEAVY.

02:12.166 --> 02:15.803
THANK GOODNESS
I'M IN SUCH...GREAT...SHAPE.

02:18.672 --> 02:19.907
LOOK AT THIS.

02:19.973 --> 02:22.710
EIGHT BAGS
OF GROCERIES, $180.

02:22.776 --> 02:26.113
YEAH. CAN YOU BELIEVE
THE FUSS THEY MADE

02:26.180 --> 02:28.349
WHEN I PAID
WITH A CHECK?

02:28.416 --> 02:31.919
CARL, YOU TOLD THEM NOT
TO CASH IT UNTIL NOVEMBER.

02:33.621 --> 02:35.456
OH, CARL,

02:35.523 --> 02:37.991
WE NEED
TO CALL A PLUMBER.

02:38.058 --> 02:40.294
WHY?

02:40.361 --> 02:41.662
LITTLE RICHIE
WAS CURIOUS TO SEE

02:41.729 --> 02:45.132
IF YOUR NEW SLIPPERS
WOULD FLOAT IN THE TOILET.

02:45.199 --> 02:47.167
THEY DON'T.

02:49.203 --> 02:51.205
DON'T WE HAVE ENOUGH
EXPENSES AROUND HERE

02:51.272 --> 02:54.542
WITHOUT THE KIDS
SABOTAGING THE PLACE?

02:54.608 --> 02:57.411
CARL, THERE ARE EIGHT PEOPLE
LIVING IN THIS HOUSE.

02:57.478 --> 02:59.112
IT'S BOUND
TO GET EXPENSIVE.

02:59.179 --> 03:00.281
IF THINGS GET TIGHT,

03:00.348 --> 03:01.882
WE'LL BOTH
WORK OVERTIME.

03:03.217 --> 03:05.286
LISTEN, YOU TWO,

03:05.353 --> 03:06.954
I FEEL LIKE
A FREELOADER.

03:07.020 --> 03:08.222
RACHEL, DON'T BE SILLY.

03:08.289 --> 03:11.058
WELL...

03:11.124 --> 03:12.693
I APPRECIATE
THE WAY YOU TWO

03:12.760 --> 03:14.462
HAVE SUPPORTED MY
ATTEMPTS TO BE A WRITER,

03:14.528 --> 03:17.631
BUT MY CAREER'S
GOING NOWHERE FAST.

03:17.698 --> 03:21.302
I'D LIKE TO CONTRIBUTE
TO THE FAMILY BUDGET.

03:21.369 --> 03:23.571
IT'S NOT NECESSARY,
RIGHT, CARL?

03:23.637 --> 03:26.640
LET'S HEAR HER OUT,
HARRIETTE.

03:26.707 --> 03:28.342
LOOK AT
THESE NEWSPAPERS.

03:28.409 --> 03:30.077
I'VE CHECKED
ALL THE WANT ADS,

03:30.143 --> 03:32.680
BUT THESE JOBS
SOUND SO LOUSY.

03:32.746 --> 03:34.014
LISTEN.

03:34.081 --> 03:37.285
"LAKESHORE ZOO SEEKS EXECUTIVE
VETERINARY ASSISTANT.

03:37.351 --> 03:39.152
SIMIAN SANITATION."

03:39.219 --> 03:40.220
WELL, THAT SOUNDS GOOD.

03:40.288 --> 03:42.089
WHAT DO YOU DO?

03:42.155 --> 03:44.625
YOU SCOOP MONKEY POOP.

03:47.428 --> 03:50.664
WHAT'S THE PAY?

03:50.731 --> 03:51.899
LISTEN RACHEL.

03:51.965 --> 03:53.033
IF YOU GOT
TO FIND A JOB,

03:53.100 --> 03:55.002
FIND SOMETHING
CHALLENGING.

03:55.068 --> 03:57.805
HEY. HERE'S
SOMETHING CHALLENGING.

03:57.871 --> 03:59.740
"SHY GUY SEEKS HOT BABE

03:59.807 --> 04:02.843
WHO SHARES LOVE
FOR PIE TOPPINGS."

04:04.812 --> 04:06.246
HEE HEE HEE.

04:07.948 --> 04:11.752
RACHEL, DON'T FEEL
THAT YOU HAVE TO TAKE

04:11.819 --> 04:13.321
THE FIRST JOB
THAT COMES ALONG.

04:13.387 --> 04:14.788
TAKE YOUR TIME, OKAY?

04:14.855 --> 04:15.889
DON'T WORRY.

04:15.956 --> 04:16.957
IT'S ALMOST IMPOSSIBLE

04:17.024 --> 04:19.927
TO FIND A JOB
THESE DAYS.

04:19.993 --> 04:20.794
GUESS WHAT.

04:20.861 --> 04:23.531
I JUST GOT A JOB.

04:26.334 --> 04:28.268
I'M A WAITRESS
AT LEROY'S.

04:28.336 --> 04:29.937
I GET MINIMUM WAGE,
PLUS TIPS.

04:30.003 --> 04:32.506
WE'RE TALKING NEW CLOTHES,
CONCERT TICKETS,

04:32.573 --> 04:34.375
* I WANT MONEY *

04:34.442 --> 04:36.510
* LOTS AND LOTS
OF MONEY *

04:36.577 --> 04:38.612
* I WANT A PIE
IN THE SKY *

04:38.679 --> 04:39.347
WHOA.

04:39.413 --> 04:40.781
* I WANT TO BE RICH *

04:40.848 --> 04:42.583
WHOA!

04:44.284 --> 04:46.454
WHAT?

04:47.355 --> 04:48.622
YOU'RE TOO YOUNG
TO HAVE A JOB.

04:48.689 --> 04:49.557
NO, I'M NOT.

04:49.623 --> 04:52.393
YOU HAVE SCHOOLWORK
AND CHORES HERE.

04:52.460 --> 04:54.528
LET ME WORK
FOR ONE MONTH.

04:54.595 --> 04:57.831
IF MY GRADES SLIP
OR I DON'T WORK HERE,

04:57.898 --> 04:59.433
I'LL QUIT.

05:01.168 --> 05:03.070
ONE MONTH.

05:03.136 --> 05:05.506
WILL YOU SIGN
MY WORK PERMIT?

05:05.573 --> 05:07.341
WHY DO YOU NEED THAT?

05:07.408 --> 05:09.643
I'M TOO YOUNG
TO HAVE A JOB.

05:10.878 --> 05:14.147
ARE THERE ANY MORE
OPENINGS AT LEROY'S?

05:14.214 --> 05:16.450
NOPE. I GOT
THE LAST ONE.

05:20.087 --> 05:21.655
YOU?

05:21.722 --> 05:24.692
YOU'RE WORKING
AT LEROY'S?

05:24.758 --> 05:27.528
I KNEW YOU'D BE
THRILLED, SUGAR KNEES.

05:29.430 --> 05:31.399
I SAW YOU ASK LEROY
FOR A JOB,

05:31.465 --> 05:34.001
SO I ASKED, TOO.

05:34.067 --> 05:35.736
GO HOME, STEVE.

05:35.803 --> 05:39.072
WAIT A MINUTE.
WAIT A MINUTE.

05:39.139 --> 05:40.207
A PECK
NEAR THE LIP AREA

05:40.273 --> 05:44.044
WOULD SPEED ME
ON MY WAY.

05:44.111 --> 05:46.814
SO WOULD A LEFT HOOK.

05:46.880 --> 05:49.983
OOH. I LOVE IT
WHEN SHE GETS PHYSICAL.

05:52.953 --> 05:54.388
BOY. LAURA'S GOT A JOB,

05:54.455 --> 05:55.689
EVEN STEVE URKEL'S
GOT ONE.

05:55.756 --> 05:57.991
I SHOULD BE ABLE
TO FIND SOMETHING.

05:58.058 --> 05:59.727
WELL, IF
YOU'RE INTERESTED,

05:59.793 --> 06:02.730
MY UNCLE CECIL URKEL
IS LOOKING FOR SOMEBODY.

06:02.796 --> 06:03.964
REALLY?

06:04.031 --> 06:05.365
WHAT JOB IS IT?

06:05.433 --> 06:06.900
I'M NOT SURE.

06:06.967 --> 06:10.137
IT'S GOT SOMETHING
TO DO WITH PIE TOPPINGS.

06:17.411 --> 06:20.013
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYS]

06:23.917 --> 06:25.085
HEY, JOLENE,

06:25.152 --> 06:29.523
WHO DO YOU THINK IS
BETTER-LOOKING, ME OR TYRONE?

06:29.590 --> 06:33.727
WELL, RIGHT NOW, EDDIE,
I'D HAVE TO SAY TYRONE.

06:33.794 --> 06:34.595
WHY?

06:34.662 --> 06:36.229
'CAUSE YOU DON'T
LOOK REAL HUNKY

06:36.296 --> 06:38.632
WITH MUSTARD
ON YOUR NOSE.

06:42.803 --> 06:45.305
LAURA, YOU'VE
TABLE SIX TO CHECK.

06:45.372 --> 06:46.940
BUT THEY'RE NOT
DONE EATING.

06:47.007 --> 06:50.243
HUH, IF I WAITED FOR PEOPLE
TO FINISH EATIN' MY FOOD...

06:50.310 --> 06:52.045
I'D NEVER MAKE A DIME.

06:58.218 --> 06:59.820
PSST.

07:01.121 --> 07:03.557
HEY! HEY! SHE LOOKS LIKE
A GREAT WAITRESS!

07:03.624 --> 07:05.759
I HOPE WE GET HER!

07:10.631 --> 07:12.566
WHAT ARE YOU GUYS
DOING HERE?

07:12.633 --> 07:14.367
WE WANTED TO GIVE
OUR SUPPORT.

07:14.434 --> 07:15.836
AND THROW YOU
SOME BUSINESS.

07:15.903 --> 07:18.706
AND AFTER THAT,
WE'LL ROCK TILL WE DROP.

07:29.983 --> 07:31.184
MOM!

07:32.820 --> 07:35.823
WAITRESS, WE NEED MENUS.

07:35.889 --> 07:38.058
SORRY, THIS IS
NOT MY STATION.

07:38.125 --> 07:39.727
STEVE, TABLE 10.

07:46.466 --> 07:47.300
HI.

07:47.367 --> 07:48.736
OH.

07:48.802 --> 07:50.437
OH, I'LL BE
WITH YOU

07:50.504 --> 07:54.274
IN TWO SHAKES OF
A LAMB'S TAIL, OKAY?

07:54.341 --> 07:55.676
HERE'S YOUR FOOD.

07:55.743 --> 07:57.477
WE'RE OUT
OF FRIES NOW,

07:57.545 --> 07:59.680
BUT I'LL TRY
AND SCRAPE SOME UP.

08:01.481 --> 08:03.416
HI, EVERYBODY.
WELCOME TO LEROY'S.

08:03.483 --> 08:05.986
MENU. MENU. MENU.

08:06.053 --> 08:07.821
MENU. MENU.

08:07.888 --> 08:09.489
JUST BRING
BURGERS AND FRIES.

08:09.557 --> 08:11.158
THANK YOU. THANK YOU.

08:11.224 --> 08:12.926
THANK YOU. THANK YOU.

08:12.993 --> 08:14.928
THANK YOU.

08:14.995 --> 08:17.831
WOULD YOU GUYS LIKE THOSE
BURGERS WITH CHEESE?

08:17.898 --> 08:19.633
PLEASE. PLEASE.

08:19.700 --> 08:22.235
OH, YOU GUYS.

08:23.203 --> 08:24.972
STEVE!

08:27.207 --> 08:28.275
OH.

08:28.341 --> 08:30.410
ALLOW ME,
MY LITTLE MILK SHAKE.

08:30.477 --> 08:32.512
NO, I'LL HANDLE IT.

08:32.580 --> 08:33.681
HANDS AS LOVELY
AS YOURS

08:33.747 --> 08:36.483
SHOULD NEVER BE
BESMIRCHED BY GREASE.

08:36.550 --> 08:38.852
OH, HERE.

08:38.919 --> 08:40.187
OH, NO!

08:44.992 --> 08:47.060
HERE, LET ME.

08:47.127 --> 08:48.028
I GOT IT.

08:48.095 --> 08:50.063
OH, NO, I INSIST.

08:53.200 --> 08:55.002
AAH!
AAH!

08:55.068 --> 08:56.870
OH, NO!

08:56.937 --> 08:58.005
OH, NO!

08:58.071 --> 08:59.773
NO!

09:04.344 --> 09:06.780
DID I DO THAT?

09:19.226 --> 09:21.194
OKAY, YOU TWO, PAYDAY.

09:21.261 --> 09:23.096
YES!

09:24.364 --> 09:26.133
YOU'RE DOING A GOOD JOB.

09:26.199 --> 09:27.601
THANKS, SIR.

09:34.374 --> 09:36.009
A BILL?

09:37.845 --> 09:40.047
THAT'S WHAT YOU OWE ME
FOR BROKEN DISHES.

09:40.113 --> 09:43.751
PERHAPS IF YOU POPPED
FOR BETTER CHINA.

09:47.788 --> 09:49.690
I SHOULD FIRE YOU.

09:49.757 --> 09:50.991
I'M IN A GOOD MOOD,

09:51.058 --> 09:53.426
SO I'LL CUT YOU
SOME SLACK.

09:53.493 --> 09:55.963
THANK YOU.
I LOVE SLACK.

09:58.666 --> 10:01.101
I'M GOING TO MAKE
A BANK DEPOSIT.

10:01.168 --> 10:02.069
TAKE YOUR TIME.

10:02.135 --> 10:04.137
WHY DON'T YOU STOP
AND TREAT YOURSELF

10:04.204 --> 10:06.239
TO A DECENT MEAL?

10:17.450 --> 10:18.919
OHH...

10:26.660 --> 10:29.029
YOU KNOW, THE LIFE OF
A RESTAURATEUR

10:29.096 --> 10:31.564
APPEALS TO
THIS PARTICULAR JOE.

10:31.631 --> 10:32.966
I'VE MASTERED WAITERING.

10:33.033 --> 10:34.634
I'M A CRACKERJACK
CASHIER,

10:34.702 --> 10:37.905
AND DURING PEAK HOURS,
A DARN GOOD HOSTESS.

10:40.207 --> 10:43.143
YUP, I THINK IT'S TIME
I BECAME A CHEF.

10:46.680 --> 10:48.148
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

10:48.215 --> 10:49.249
TO TURN ON THE GRILL.

10:49.316 --> 10:52.352
I'LL FRY YOU UP
A STEVE-O SUPREMO.

10:53.854 --> 10:55.956
URKEL, YOU SHOULDN'T
DO ANY COOKING.

10:56.023 --> 10:57.524
DON'T FRET, MY PET.

10:57.590 --> 10:59.760
WHAT COULD GO WRONG?

11:29.522 --> 11:31.925
DID I DO THAT?

11:52.312 --> 11:53.280
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

11:53.346 --> 11:55.115
LEROY'S IS ON FIRE.

11:58.618 --> 12:00.153
LAURA.

12:07.828 --> 12:09.162
LAURA!

12:10.597 --> 12:11.832
LAURA. OH, MY BABY.

12:11.899 --> 12:13.100
ARE YOU OKAY?

12:13.166 --> 12:15.168
I'M FINE, MA.

12:27.047 --> 12:27.981
LAURA!

12:28.048 --> 12:28.515
DAD!

12:28.581 --> 12:31.418
LAURA!

12:31.484 --> 12:33.053
OH, SWEETHEART.

12:33.120 --> 12:35.255
I WAS SO WORRIED.
ARE YOU ALRIGHT?

12:35.322 --> 12:36.589
FINE, DAD.

12:36.656 --> 12:38.225
OH, SWEETHEART.

13:03.650 --> 13:05.318
OOH.
OOH.
OOH.

13:33.746 --> 13:35.782
I'VE BEEN LOOKING
FOR YOU TWO.

13:35.849 --> 13:37.918
NOW JUST HOW DID
THIS FIRE START?

13:37.985 --> 13:39.419
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT,
YOUR HONOR.

13:39.486 --> 13:41.955
I'M NOT THE JUDGE.
I'M THE FIRE INSPECTOR.

13:42.022 --> 13:45.525
I KNOW. I WAS JUST
PRACTICING.

13:45.592 --> 13:46.793
HERE'S WHAT HAPPENED.

13:46.860 --> 13:48.295
SOME GREASE FLARED UP
ON THE GRILL.

13:48.361 --> 13:49.829
STILL WE COULD'VE
HANDLED IT.

13:49.897 --> 13:51.498
BUT THEN HE
THREW WATER ON IT.

13:51.564 --> 13:55.668
OH! NO, NO, NO. YOU NEVER EVER
THROW WATER ON A GREASE FIRE.

13:55.735 --> 13:58.371
THANKS. I'LL KNOW
FOR THE NEXT TIME.

14:12.352 --> 14:13.987
LEROY.

14:14.054 --> 14:15.455
HOW YOU HOLDING UP?

14:15.522 --> 14:17.958
I'VE HAD BETTER DAYS.

14:21.228 --> 14:22.162
YOU!

14:22.229 --> 14:23.163
AAH!

14:23.230 --> 14:26.233
LEROY, NO, NO! CALM DOWN!
TAKE IT EASY!

14:26.299 --> 14:28.936
YOU CAN REBUILD
THE PLACE BETTER THAN EVER.

14:29.802 --> 14:31.371
I'M TOO OLD
TO START OVER.

14:31.438 --> 14:33.740
I'M RETIRING
TO FORT LAUDERDALE,

14:33.806 --> 14:35.943
GET ME
A LITTLE CO-OP.

14:36.009 --> 14:37.010
YOU DON'T
MEAN THAT, LEROY.

14:37.077 --> 14:39.512
I'M TAKING
MY INSURANCE MONEY,

14:39.579 --> 14:41.881
MAYBE EVEN MY WIFE.

14:41.949 --> 14:43.883
I HAVE FLIPPED
MY LAST BURGER.

14:43.951 --> 14:46.486
NOW THE ONLY BUNS
I WANT TO SEE

14:46.553 --> 14:49.056
ARE ON THE BEACH.

14:49.122 --> 14:53.193
BOY, HE GOT UP ON
THE WRONG SIDE OF THE BED.

15:05.038 --> 15:07.407
DOES EVERYBODY
HAVE NAME TAGS?

15:07.474 --> 15:11.511
STEVE, CARL AND I
KNOW EACH OTHER.

15:11.578 --> 15:13.146
JUST GOING BY THE BOOK.

15:13.213 --> 15:16.316
WELCOME, EVERYBODY.
THIS IS AN INFORMAL MEETING.

15:16.383 --> 15:19.786
FEEL FREE TO ASK
ANY QUESTIONS AT ANY TIME.

15:19.852 --> 15:20.820
YES?

15:20.887 --> 15:23.423
WHY ARE WE HERE?

15:23.490 --> 15:24.491
GOOD QUESTION...

15:24.557 --> 15:25.825
CARL.

15:25.892 --> 15:27.327
HEE HEE HEE.
[SNORT SNORT]

15:28.528 --> 15:31.064
AND I'LL ANSWER IT.

15:31.131 --> 15:33.333
YOU SEE, UM...

15:33.400 --> 15:35.068
WHEN STEVE
BURNED DOWN LEROY'S,

15:35.135 --> 15:37.370
IT CAUSED
LOTS OF PROBLEMS.

15:37.437 --> 15:39.372
THE NEIGHBORHOOD KIDS
LOST THEIR HANGOUT,

15:39.439 --> 15:41.241
STEVE AND LAURA
LOST THEIR JOBS,

15:41.308 --> 15:44.944
AND POOR LEROY
LOST HIS MIND.

15:45.012 --> 15:47.280
AT THE SAME TIME,
I WAS LOOKING FOR A JOB

15:47.347 --> 15:49.549
AND GETTING
ABSOLUTELY NOWHERE.

15:49.616 --> 15:52.552
THAT'S WHEN I DUG
INTO THE OLD GRAY MATTER

15:52.619 --> 15:56.256
AND YANKED OUT AN IDEA THAT
REEKED OF SHEER GENIUS.

15:58.158 --> 16:00.193
STEVE SUGGESTED
THAT I BUY LEROY'S,

16:00.260 --> 16:03.396
REBUILD IT, AND RUN IT
AS MY OWN BUSINESS.

16:03.463 --> 16:05.265
WHOA!

16:05.332 --> 16:07.267
IT'S THE ANSWER
TO EVERYONE'S PROBLEMS.

16:07.334 --> 16:10.970
BUT WHERE WILL YOU GET MONEY
TO BUY A RESTAURANT?

16:11.038 --> 16:13.806
WELL, FROM THE BANK
AND MY...

16:13.873 --> 16:16.376
BRAND-NEW PARTNERS.

16:18.345 --> 16:20.680
I THINK SHE MEANS US...

16:20.747 --> 16:22.515
CARL.

16:25.185 --> 16:27.054
THE BANK
WILL FINANCE US

16:27.120 --> 16:29.456
IF WE CAN COME UP WITH
A 20% DOWN PAYMENT.

16:29.522 --> 16:32.825
I'LL USE THE INSURANCE MONEY
MY HUSBAND LEFT ME.

16:32.892 --> 16:36.563
ALL I NEED FROM YOU
IS A CHECK FOR...

16:39.899 --> 16:42.669
WHOA.

16:42.735 --> 16:43.870
I KNOW I CAN
MAKE IT WORK.

16:43.936 --> 16:46.673
I REALLY BELIEVE THAT
WITH ALL MY HEART.

16:46.739 --> 16:49.509
RACHEL, WE'VE PLENTY OF
CONFIDENCE IN YOU BUT...

16:49.576 --> 16:52.445
AREN'T RESTAURANTS
A RISKY INVESTMENT?

16:52.512 --> 16:53.546
STEVE?

16:53.613 --> 16:54.914
GOOD QUESTION.

16:54.981 --> 16:56.149
THE FOLLOWING
VISUAL AID

16:56.216 --> 16:59.286
WILL CLEAR UP ANY
AND ALL DOUBTS YOU HAVE.

16:59.352 --> 17:02.322
[IMITATES
TRUMPET FANFARE]

17:07.394 --> 17:10.163
OH, JUST
PULL OFF THE SHEET!

17:12.332 --> 17:15.135
I GIVE YOU
RACHEL'S PLACE.

17:19.939 --> 17:21.674
CARL,
IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

17:21.741 --> 17:25.112
I SOUGHT THE ADVICE OF
THE WORLD'S BEST CPA,

17:25.178 --> 17:28.215
MY OWN UNCLE
HIRAM ROSS URKEL.

17:28.281 --> 17:30.683
ACCORDING TO
H. AND R. URKEL...

17:31.884 --> 17:33.986
RACHEL'S PLACE
SHOULD TURN A PROFIT

17:34.053 --> 17:35.855
IN LESS THAN ONE YEAR.

17:35.922 --> 17:37.624
HOW DOES HE KNOW?

17:37.690 --> 17:39.159
IT'S AN INVERSE CURVE.

17:39.226 --> 17:40.793
RISING NEIGHBORHOOD
POPULATION GROWTH

17:40.860 --> 17:44.964
VERSUS DECLINING FRANCHISES
THAT SERVE MEAT.

17:45.031 --> 17:46.533
OH.

17:48.501 --> 17:51.271
WE'LL LET YOU DISCUSS
THE PROPOSITION.

17:51.338 --> 17:53.806
IF YOU DECIDE
TO INVEST, GREAT.

17:53.873 --> 17:55.308
IF YOU DECIDE NOT TO,

17:55.375 --> 17:58.678
BELIEVE ME, IT'S OKAY.
I UNDERSTAND.

18:07.454 --> 18:10.257
WELL, HONEY,
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

18:10.323 --> 18:12.091
IT'S AN INTERESTING
PROPOSAL.

18:12.159 --> 18:14.394
I BELIEVE RACHEL
COULD HANDLE IT.

18:14.461 --> 18:18.131
IT'S OBVIOUS SHE REALLY
WANTS TO DO THIS.

18:18.198 --> 18:19.466
BUT I FEEL
UNCOMFORTABLE

18:19.532 --> 18:22.269
ABOUT ASKING YOU TO PUT UP
SO MUCH FOR MY SISTER.

18:22.335 --> 18:23.770
YOU WORKED HARD
FOR THAT MONEY.

18:23.836 --> 18:25.405
NO, NO, NO.

18:25.472 --> 18:27.574
WE WORKED HARD
FOR THAT MONEY.

18:27.640 --> 18:29.576
SWEETHEART,
RACHEL IS FAMILY,

18:29.642 --> 18:32.879
NOT JUST YOUR FAMILY,
BUT OUR FAMILY.

18:32.945 --> 18:35.815
BUT LIKE YOU SAID, A RESTAURANT
IS A RISKY BUSINESS.

18:37.684 --> 18:39.319
YEAH, IT'S A GAMBLE,

18:39.386 --> 18:41.388
BUT OUR ODDS
ARE A LOT BETTER

18:41.454 --> 18:44.257
IF WE BET ON
SOMEBODY WE LOVE.

18:44.324 --> 18:45.658
SO YOU WANT TO DO IT?

18:45.725 --> 18:46.559
ABSOLUTELY.

18:46.626 --> 18:48.295
OH, CARL.

18:48.361 --> 18:50.730
I JUST WISH WE COULD.

18:55.134 --> 18:57.069
WHAT?

18:57.136 --> 18:58.638
WELL, HONEY,

18:58.705 --> 19:02.275
RACHEL NEEDS JUST A LITTLE BIT
MORE MONEY THAN WE HAVE.

19:03.610 --> 19:05.278
OH?

19:07.680 --> 19:09.148
YOU SEE...

19:09.216 --> 19:10.550
THE THING IS,

19:10.617 --> 19:12.419
A COUPLE
OF MONTHS AGO,

19:12.485 --> 19:15.388
LIEUTENANT MURTAGH...

19:15.455 --> 19:18.558
HE GAVE ME A GOOD TIP
ON A SWEET LITTLE STOCK,

19:18.625 --> 19:21.160
SO...I INVESTED.

19:23.696 --> 19:25.665
HOW MUCH, CARL?

19:28.100 --> 19:29.636
5 GRAND.

19:30.703 --> 19:33.940
CARL! WELL, CAN'T YOU
SELL THE STOCK

19:34.006 --> 19:35.007
AND GET THE MONEY BACK?

19:35.074 --> 19:37.610
THE STOCK HAS GONE DOWN.

19:37.677 --> 19:40.347
WE'D ONLY HAVE ENOUGH
MONEY TO GO BOWLING.

19:40.413 --> 19:43.516
ONE OF US, ANYWAY.

19:44.984 --> 19:47.420
CARL, WE'LL DISCUSS
THIS LATER.

19:47.487 --> 19:48.755
BUT IN THE MEANTIME,

19:48.821 --> 19:51.624
YOU BETTER PRAY THAT STOCK
GOES BACK UP.

19:52.659 --> 19:54.661
RACHEL!

19:57.029 --> 19:58.998
DID I KEEP YOU WAITING?

19:59.065 --> 20:00.367
RACHEL, UH...

20:00.433 --> 20:03.936
WE TALKED IT OVER, AND WE
DECIDED WE WANT TO HELP.

20:04.003 --> 20:05.171
OHH! OH, YES!

20:05.238 --> 20:07.106
OH, THANK YOU SO MUCH.

20:07.173 --> 20:09.175
BUT--BUT...

20:09.242 --> 20:12.679
WE'RE A FEW THOUSAND SHORT
OF WHAT YOU NEED.

20:13.079 --> 20:14.113
OH.

20:14.180 --> 20:16.182
I'M SO SORRY, RACHEL.

20:16.249 --> 20:18.851
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

20:18.918 --> 20:20.853
IT JUST WASN'T
MEANT TO BE.

20:23.390 --> 20:24.624
HOW DARE YOU PEOPLE

20:24.691 --> 20:26.826
HAVE AN INVESTORS' MEETING
WITHOUT ME?

20:26.893 --> 20:27.460
MAMA--

20:27.527 --> 20:29.061
IF NOT FOR STEVE,

20:29.128 --> 20:31.798
I'D STILL BE OUT BACK
SHOOTING HOOPS.

20:33.833 --> 20:35.502
HERE.

20:36.669 --> 20:38.905
MOTHER WINSLOW,
THIS IS A BLANK CHECK.

20:38.971 --> 20:41.741
YOU'RE PRETTY SWIFT.

20:41.808 --> 20:43.710
WE NEED $5,000.

20:43.776 --> 20:46.946
WRITE IN A NUMBER.
WHATEVER YOU NEED.

20:47.013 --> 20:48.515
YOU HAVE THE MONEY?

20:48.581 --> 20:52.585
IS A FROG'S BUTT
WATERTIGHT?

20:54.053 --> 20:55.322
WRITE IT.

20:55.388 --> 20:57.824
OH, MOTHER WINSLOW,
THANK YOU SO MUCH!

21:31.558 --> 21:32.825
IN A FEW MOMENTS,

21:32.892 --> 21:35.495
WE'LL UNLOCK THAT DOOR
AND MAKE HISTORY,

21:35.562 --> 21:38.898
NOT TO MENTION
A WHOLE LOT OF MONEY.

21:38.965 --> 21:39.966
A TOAST.

21:40.032 --> 21:42.702
TO RACHEL'S PLACE
AND ITS BEAUTIFUL OWNER.

21:42.769 --> 21:44.003
THANK YOU.

21:44.070 --> 21:45.372
HEAR, HEAR!

21:45.438 --> 21:46.639
WAIT, WAIT. ONE MORE.

21:46.706 --> 21:47.774
LET'S DRINK
TO THE PERSON

21:47.840 --> 21:50.076
WHO REALLY
MADE THIS POSSIBLE--

21:50.142 --> 21:52.211
OUR JUNIOR PARTNER
ESTELLE WINSLOW.

21:52.278 --> 21:53.813
HEAR, HEAR!

21:54.514 --> 21:55.915
COME ON, LET'S DANCE.

21:55.982 --> 21:59.852
I CAN'T WAIT TO GET DOWN
WITH MY BAD SELF.

22:05.492 --> 22:07.394
I WANT TO THANK
THIS YOUNG MAN

22:07.460 --> 22:10.397
WHO HOLDS A SPECIAL
PLACE IN MY HEART.

22:10.463 --> 22:11.631
WE WOULDN'T
BE HERE TODAY

22:11.698 --> 22:16.102
IF HE HADN'T BURNT
THIS PLACE DOWN.

22:16.168 --> 22:17.837
TO STEVE URKEL.

22:17.904 --> 22:20.039
YEAH, STEVE.

22:20.106 --> 22:21.674
AH, THANKS, EVERYBODY.

22:21.741 --> 22:23.410
AND WE'LL
ALL HAVE BURGERS.

22:23.476 --> 22:25.277
I'LL JUST
FIRE UP THE GRILL.

22:25.344 --> 22:26.112
ISN'T THAT CUTE?

22:26.178 --> 22:27.880
FIRE UP THE GRILL?

22:27.947 --> 22:29.682
DON'T TOUCH THAT GRILL!
